description: Yulia Navalnaya, the widow of Alexei Navalny, attended an anti-Putin election protest in Berlin on Sunday along with other top Russian opposition leaders.
title: With Russian opposition exiled, Berlin becomes center of anti-Putin protest

description: It was the fourth eruption in three months on the Reykjanes Peninsula, around the town of Grindavik and the Blue Lagoon. Local media live-streamed the lava flows.
title: Icelandic volcano erupts, turning sky orange and forcing evacuations

description: New restrictions to the U.S. asylum system are under consideration by the Biden administration following the collapse of the bipartisan border bill.
title: Biden toughened asylum screening. It won’t contain a new border surge.

description: Powerful photos of recent weeks in Haiti, which has been embroiled in protests, gang-related violence, prison break ins and a change in leadership.
title: Haiti’s descent into chaos, in photos

description: Russians formed queues outside polling stations at precisely noon Sunday to protest an election with only one possible outcome: Vladimir Putin’s victory.
title: Russians protest Putin’s forever rule with long lines at polling stations

description: U.S. charity World Central Kitchen said nearly 200 tons of food from one ship has arrived in Gaza, which is on the brink of famine. Another shipment is planned.
title: Food being readied for distribution after first aid ship reaches Gaza

description: The Pentagon’s widening role reflects both Biden’s staunch support for Israel and his mounting frustration with how it has prosecuted the war in Gaza.
title: As Gaza war rages, U.S. military footprint expands across Middle East

description: The announcement came on the heels of a visit by an American delegation. Until last year, Niger had been a key U.S. military partner in West Africa.
title: Niger junta announces end to military relationship with United States
